            "Then He brought me to the entrance of the courtyard, and when I looked, behold, a hole in the wall.",
            "And He said to me, \u201cSon of man, now dig through the wall.\u201d So I dug through the wall, and behold, an entrance.",
            "Then He said to me, \u201cGo in and see the wicked abominations that they are committing here.\u201d",
            "So I entered and looked, and behold, every form of crawling things and animals and detestable things, with all the idols of the house of Israel, were carved on the wall all around.",
